<p>The decorative icons and motifs throughout this site are from <em>Design Motifs of Ancient Mexico</em> by Jorge Enciso: a collection of copyright-free designs reproduced from carved seals of pre-Columbian cultures including the Aztec, Maya, Totonac, Zapotec, Olmec, and Toltec.</p>
<footer class="attribution">
  <p><em>Design Motifs of Ancient Mexico</em> by Jorge Enciso (1879–1969). New York: Dover Publications, 1953. 153 pp.</p>
  <p>766 copyright-free designs reproduced from carved seals of the Aztec, Maya, Totonac, Zapotec, Olmec, Toltec, and other early Mexican cultures. Translation of <em>Sellos del antiguo México</em>.</p>
  <p>Source: <a href="https://archive.org/details/designmotifsofan0000enci" rel="noopener noreferrer">Internet Archive</a> · ISBN 0-486-20084-1</p>
</footer>